### SmartRiver environment variables (example)
### Copy to `.env` and update values.

## Database
# PostgreSQL (optional; current backend also uses SQLite by default for auth/feedback)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/smartriver

# SQLite path used by backend repository (auth + feedback persistence)
SMARTRIVER_SQLITE_PATH=backend/db/smartriver.sqlite3

## Auth / JWT
# Used by backend/auth/auth_service.py (prefers JWT_SECRET_KEY, falls back to SECRET_KEY)
JWT_SECRET_KEY=your-jwt-secret-change-in-production
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-change-in-production
ALGORITHM=HS256
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=60

## Backend app
APP_ENV=development
DEBUG=true
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

